  "time_ut": 1662029101,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u200c\u0da7 \u0d91\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0dc4\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc3\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db7\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "A judge withdraws from hearing the petition against Duminda",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Supreme Court Justice Priyantha Jayawardene withdrew from the hearing of the petition filed in the Supreme Court requesting to invalidate the order issued by the President to release the 11th accused in the murder case of Bharata Lakshman Premachanadra and former Member of Parliament Mr. Duminda Silva under a presidential amnesty while he was sentenced to death. It was informed today (01) that",
        "These facts were revealed when the Supreme Court re-heard these petitions filed by three people including former Member of Parliament Hirunika Premachandra today (01).",
        "This petition was taken into consideration today (01) before a Supreme Court bench consisting of Mr. Priyantha Jayawardena, Mr. Yasanta Kodagoda and Mr. Arjuna Obeysekera.",
        "The court also issued an interim order preventing the execution of the presidential pardon granted to Mr. Duminda Silva in a previous hearing and he was remanded in custody and the Supreme Court had also given permission to hold the petition hearing.",
        "This petition was filed before the Supreme Court by former Member of Parliament Hirunika Premachandra on July 20, 2021.",
        "Instead of the President, the Attorney General and the Minister of Justice, R. Mr. Duminda Silva and the Attorney General have been nominated.",
        "The complainant stated that after conducting a full trial regarding the murder in front of a three-judge panel of the High Court, the respondent Mr. Duminda Silva was found guilty and sentenced to death on September 8, 2016 by a two-thirds majority decision. His petition has been mentioned.",
        "In spite of this, the petitioner had mentioned in her petition that the president had granted amnesty.",
        "Accordingly, Mrs. Hirunika Premachandra informed the Supreme Court in her petition that the release was not made in accordance with the provisions of the Constitution and therefore the release is unconstitutional."
      ],
